HEADWORD: Immensity
<hw>Im*men"si*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Immensities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>immensitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>immensit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The state or quality of being immense; inlimited or immeasurable
extension; infinity; vastness in extent or bulk; greatness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lost in the wilds of vast <qex>immensity</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackmore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>immensity</qex> of the material system.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immensive</ent>⟦br⟧
